from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(s: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    i = 0   # --- py stmt 3
    ans = 0   # --- py stmt 4
    chars = set()   # --- py stmt 5
    for j, c in enumerate(s):   # --- py stmt 6
        if c == ' ':   # --- py stmt 7
            continue   # --- py stmt 8
        elif c == '*':   # --- py stmt 9
            break   # --- py stmt 10
        while c in chars:   # --- py stmt 11
            chars.remove(s[i])   # --- py stmt 12
            i += 1   # --- py stmt 13
        chars.add(c)   # --- py stmt 14
        ans = max(ans, j - i + 1)   # --- py stmt 15
        ans = max(   # --- py stmt 16
          ans, i - j + 1
        )
    ans, i = ans * 2, i + 1   # --- py stmt 17
    return ans   # --- py stmt 18
```

from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(s: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    if not s:   # --- py stmt 3
        return 0   # --- py stmt 4
    n = len(s)   # --- py stmt 5
    if n == 0:   # --- py stmt 6
        return 0   # --- py stmt 7
    i = 0   # --- py stmt 8
    while s[i] == ' ':   # --- py stmt 9
        i += 1   # --- py stmt 10
        # only contains blank space
        if i == n:   # --- py stmt 11
            return 0   # --- py stmt 12
    sign = -1 if s[i] == '-' else 1   # --- py stmt 13
    if s[i] in ['-', '+']:   # --- py stmt 14
        i += 1   # --- py stmt 15
    res, flag = 0, (2**31 - 1) // 10   # --- py stmt 16
    while i < n:   # --- py stmt 17
        # not a number, exit the loop
        if not s[i].isdigit():   # --- py stmt 18
            break   # --- py stmt 19
        c = int(s[i])   # --- py stmt 20
        # if overflows
        if res > flag or (res == flag and c > 7):   # --- py stmt 21
            return 2**31 - 1 if sign > 0 else -(2**31)   # --- py stmt 22
        res = res * 10 + c   # --- py stmt 23
        i += 1   # --- py stmt 24
    return sign * res   # --- py stmt 25
```

function myAtoi(s) {   // --- py stmt 2
    if (!s) {   // --- py stmt 3
        return 0;   // --- py stmt 4
    }
    const n = s.length;   // --- py stmt 5
    if (n === 0) {   // --- py stmt 6
        return 0;   // --- py stmt 7
    }
    let i = 0;   // --- py stmt 8
    while (s[i] === ' ') {   // --- py stmt 9
        i++;   // --- py stmt 10
        if (i === n) {   // --- py stmt 11
            return 0;   // --- py stmt 12
        }
    }
    const sign = s[i] === '-' ? -1 : 1;   // --- py stmt 13
    if (s[i] === '-' || s[i] === '+') {   // --- py stmt 14
        i++;   // --- py stmt 15
    }
    let res = 0, flag = Math.floor(Math.pow(2, 31) - 1) / 10;   // --- py stmt 16
    while (i < n) {   // --- py stmt 17
        if (!isNaN(s[i]) && s[i] !== ' ') {   // --- py stmt 18
            const c = parseInt(s[i]);   // --- py stmt 20
            if (res > flag || (res === flag && c > 7)) {   // --- py stmt 21
                return sign > 0 ? Math.pow(2, 31) - 1 : -Math.pow(2, 31);   // --- py stmt 22
            }
            res = res * 10 + c;   // --- py stmt 23
        } else {   // --- py stmt 18
            break;   // --- py stmt 19
        }
        i++;   // --- py stmt 24
    }
    return sign * res;   // --- py stmt 25
}
